      "stem_html": "<p>Arginine, the most basic of the 20 common amino acids, contains a <i>guanidino</i> functional group in its side chain. Explain, using resonance structures to show how the protonated guanidino group is stabilized.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcnNaIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--903eba54c1789d0a92eed94dd92c21d092340543/OChem_26_EC_019.jpg\" alt=\"The structure of L- arginine in which the guanidino group is labeled. It comprises wedged bonded  C1 amine cation and carboxylate ion.\">",
